The paper discusses the design of a self size-estimating feed-forward network using optimization techniques for learning weight matrices, number of nodes, and layers. This falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning, which is covered by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of activation functions and optimization techniques for classification accuracy, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of the network for classification tasks suggests that it may also be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the mention of consistent performance across Monte-Carlo trials suggests that the paper may also be relevant to control systems (cs.SY).
